  <em>
    <strong>"Holy sh*tsnacks! Krieger's one of the boys from Brazil!"</strong>
  </em>
</blockquote> Yes, once again I find myself reading a book as a result of an <i>
  <a title="Archer FX" href="http://www.fxnetworks.com/archer" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Archer</a>
</i> reference (see also <b>
  <a title="Bartleby the Scrivener Review" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/717453317" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Bartleby The Scrivener</a>
</b>). The premise (of the book, not of Archer) is that down in South America, the fugitive Dr. Mengele is sending out six men to kill 94 civil servants on precise dates in nine countries. <br><br>Renowned Nazi-hunter, Yakov Liebermann receives a mysterious phone call from a twenty-something American boy who went down Brazil to investigate and (no big spoiler here) is killed. As Krieger would say, <em>schiesse</em>!<br><br><a href="http://imgur.com/p3C2NfV" rel="nofollow noopener">
