    <a title="Frances" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6115184-frances"><img alt="Frances" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483254731p2/6115184.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/877603171?book_show_action=true">Mar 10, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Frances" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Frances" href="/user/show/6115184-frances">Frances</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781849015905" href="/book/show/9633082-the-boys-from-brazil">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer877603171" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3579810624784858586">I love Ira levin&apos;s work. Now I just need to find one of his books that&apos;s not so famous that I already know the big twist.<br/><br/>Great book, some great symbolism carefully worked into it. Levin was very good at presenting ideas as fact and never glorifying. I won&apos;t dissect the plot at length but it&apos;s good to be reminded that &quot;Those who cannot remember the past are condemned to repeat it&quot; (ta, Santayana) and I just love books on alternate history. </span>
  <span id="freeText3579810624784858586" style="display:none">I love Ira levin's work. Now I just need to find one of his books that's not so famous that I already know the big twist.<br /><br />Great book, some great symbolism carefully worked into it. Levin was very good at presenting ideas as fact and never glorifying. I won't dissect the plot at length but it's good to be reminded that "Those who cannot remember the past are condemned to repeat it" (ta, Santayana) and I just love books on alternate history. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3579810624784858586" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

